      "id": "4d1fcf0840d4cfb0",
      "text": "The growth of a community culture is used purposefully with the “Reluctant Time Travellers” (RTTs) in EH’s “Cultural Leap” (CL) initiative.  RTTs are people who have been displaced by the Leap and have yet to find their sense of identity. CL offers activities for enjoyment, making friends and helping RTTs to structure their new found leisure time. CL builds on humankind’s deep sense of story. The content of CL sessions means that RTTs become immersed in aspects of EH culture. That cultural immersion helps them place their personal experiences in the context of our wider shared story. This is deeply therapeutic and helps them find their new sense of identity, purpose and belonging.\n\n"
